76561198040108750,Recommended,329190,14437806,"Posted: 11 February, 2015",all,Coconut Bandit,"""FINAL"" version updateDespite not being finished Volo is still a great game.If you want to experience way well done wingsuit simulation wether in VR or not, forget all the Steep nonsense and jump into Volo.You can fly for 30 seconds or about 2 minutes of intense ride, if you master the winds you can stay in air for about 5-15 minutes of cruising. It's a game that doesn't take much of your time yet offers a chill and thrill like no other, it's a unique experience - just like wingsuits themselves.You may not get the full product and super pimped up graphic of a wingsuiter, but take it from others that played this game for long - the blue man grows on you very naturally, while not being realistic it's simplicity offers great insight into whats going on in air and with jumpers body while minimalistic design allows you to connect better to the actual experience of what's going on all around you, it doesn't distracts you with outstanding textures and pixel shader 2000... scenery does, and HS it's gorgeus.Flight's not easy, you have to learn it, it's gratifying.Forget your counter strike instincts, let yourself chill with very minimal mouse movements as you go downhill 200km/h.(pro tip) Trace this OO slowly with cursor as if you were drawing infinity symbol, thta's how you play Volo with mouse.IF you feel like flying, give Volo a try.Thank you devs for this trip! I keep coming back from time to time :)[Early Access v.3.4]""One minute was enough, Tyler said, a person had to work hard for it, but a minute of perfection was worth the effort.  A moment was the most you could ever expect from perfection."" -Chuck Palahniuk, Fight Club[Long version! (scroll down for short one)]What is it?- a game about flyingHow long does it take?- single jump can be anything between a couple seconds, up to about 10 minutes for now, with an averge speed flight close to earth being about 60-120 seconds... so not really long, but ""A moment was the most you could ever expect from perfection.""What's the story?- for now: You got kicked out of heaven, you have very short time to live; Learn to fly or die.Make the most of the time you have left, soar through air, fly as close to earth as you can, fly as fast as possible, find the way to never touch the ground, enjoy the stunning sunset above beautiful mountains as your short life as a blue stickman angel comes to an end. There's but a one rule for now - ground is lava.What can i do in it?- master the art of flying, gliding, proximity flying, some other technical terms, AND CANNONBALLING!- download players made challange paths (fromVolo forum)make your own paths and fly them as fast as you can- fly around seeking new paths to fly, new winds to use, making stunts along the way just for the thrills- select a spawn point from which you begin- change the camera view (left foot and right foot(GoPro style), first person, third person, frontal, and free view(two last not really usefull for flying but you can get nice photos ;D))Is it easy to play?- Not at all! For now there's no tutorial, but that's not a big problem since the controls are intuitive and it sets your brain on fire - first, to survive the fall, then to fly as far as you can, finally to fly as close to earth as possible doing stunts while flying as long as you can. It can be frustrating at the beginning, since your experience with it won't be like the trailer, but if you put your mind to it, you'll quickly learn to fly and begin to understand the mastery of the Art of flying!Is it worth it?- depends on how much you're fascinated by flying.If you dig skydiving, wingsuits, basejumping and all that stuff, i think you'll love this game!Despiting not much of content (for now), the game already offers amazing physics to play with, along with captivating gfx. It all feels very natural and realistic.It's challenging - don't only limit yourself to flying as fast as possible. Do cannonballs, make turns, spin around, fly on your back, learn the winds and how to use them and you'll be flying for many minutes in a single jump.Create the crazy course using all of the above and see how fast can you and others make it!The devs are active and communicating with players, and there's a lot of stuff to come![Short version]What can i do for now?+ fly with wingsuit stickman+ select a spawn point+ create, share and download fly courses (sharing and download via Volo forum)+ perform some stunts while flying+ use controllers as well as kb&mouse+ die infinite numbers of times by all kinds of unsuspected wind changes while flying at high velocities straight into the ground or mountains... or just pure suiciding :PWhat can't i do for now?- make the jump by yourself- use parachute to land safelyWhat's in there to come?+ Please, see the officialEarly Access infoAs anordinary player, for now i'd give it a strong5/10As anenthusiastthat looks for the game about wingsuits, that would give you the thrill of realistic flight, not story based and long, but captivating and moment taking, the score is7/10for now.Finally, when the game spreads it's wings (more content), make the score9/10Final word?I say Volo Airsport is well worth the price as it is now.Some may disagree; it's all about seeing and living the moment and will to master the art of stickman flight. It seems simple, but it's hard to master, with a lot of place to play around with pyshics and aerodynamics.I found nothing better after a stressfull day, than to put my headphones on, play some sweet music and fly the stress out!"
