76561198106025595,Recommended,329190,13300734,"Posted: 9 December, 2014",all,CrimsonGamer99,"I don't write many reviews, but this game is special, so I ought to start...-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Overview: Volo Airsport is an amazing game that is currently under early development by the same people who brought you the Aurora Wager (a steampunk-style balloon race to get to the north pole). Volo is all about the freedom of flight in a wingsuit. It is different from other games because it has no real competition, leaderboards, or main goals (as of yet). There are no winners or losers, only people who learn to soar, and those who master the art of faceplanting.--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Pros:-Great developer-Cheap price ($13 as of now)-Tiny file size (almost 500mb, takes 3 minutes to download)-Amazing graphics-Oculus Rift and gamepad support-Stunning physics and aerodynamics-Wind and sound very clean and smooth-Friendly developers (have had a chat with Ramjet Anvil and Frank V. more than once about Volo)-Future plans to include parachutes and such--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Cons:-Like all indie games, it is still under development and has multiple bugs-Character model rather simple, just a blue human figure (red if you crash hard)-No real goal or point (but that may be the idea of the game, just a stress reliever)-Extremely simple, but controls are difficult (using keyboard)-No instructions or tutorial, you are (literally) thrown off a cliff and told to fly---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Overall, if you are reading this, then you must be considering getting Volo. I have one word of advice:Buy it."
