76561198013971147,Recommended,329190,24793493,"Posted: 9 August, 2016",all,Kale77,"This game's fantastic, BUY IT.I was just browsing Steam casually the other night and stumbled upon this gem. I was getting it for my Vive, but tbh it's superb without it. If you hold any interest in a wingsuit BASE jumping title (or just flying in general), Volo Airsport will fill that craving nicely.Just be aware it's still early. Duh, ""Early Access"". But where it counts, this game NAILS it. It does an marvelous job of conveying the sensation and speed (shaking camera) of flight. You never feel quite in total control, just someone who is delicately urging chaos in the right direction. It always feels like you're right on the edge of success or failure. This makes skimming a few feet through a jagged ravine and barely blasting out the exit or cornering around large cliffs with your arm almost touching the side at 120 mph completely exhilirating. There's a decent learning curve to understanding the nuances of the physics model and how much a light touch is benficial to effective control, so becoming skilled requires patience, practice, and a LOT of 100+ mph faceplants. I do question the physics at times as your character can flop around like a piece of paper in situations, and there are ridiculous recoveries possible that'd be laughable in real life, but even still it accomplishes what I think it would feel like to pilot wingsuits....and that's what's vital.At $12 it's a steal, but it's VERY bare bones. It's essentially a tech demo with no additional content aside from six peaks to jump with a few lines each, but built on an engine that holds tremedous potential. If content matters to you you may want to think twice as at this stage Volo Airsport's more about experimenting with wingsuit fllight dynamics, perfecting them, and navigating courses. There's no selection of pilots, equipment, timed mode, multiplayer (in the works), career mode, none of it. I mean, the pilot doesn't even have a fully textured or realistic model. The courses are limited and do get repetitive so this is at this point great in short bursts.But don't let these things dissuade you if you enjoy games about flight as the game's still being worked on. More content is coming, and there's supposedly a course editor in the works. While I struggle to recommend tech demos, I cannot recommend this one enough as the gameplay is exemplary so I'd encourage people to purcahse this as it will enable the developers to keep expanding on it. Volo Airsport deserves nothing less.If you've ever wanted to soar like a bird high and scream like an eagle low without actually risking becoming a pancake, here's your chance. Take the leap."
